        <abstract> 
<p>Some questions on errata in second English issue of <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>.</p>  
<p>Sends a paper by Robert Hartmann on domestic animals of the countries bordering the Nile ["Geographische Verbreitung der im nordöstlichen Afrika wild lebenden Säugethiere" <hi rend="italic">Z. Ges. Erdkd. Berlin</hi> 3 (1868): 28–69, 232–70, 345–68, 404–20].</p> 
            <p>Has thought much about CD’s theory of Pangenesis. It "seems rather a little too complicated … as a molecular theory".</p>
        </abstract>
